ala and Java APIs are updated?\r\n* [ ] Have you updated the documentation for both Scala and Java sections?\r\n* [x] Have you added tests for any changed functionality?\r\n\r\n# Helpful things\r\n\r\n## Fixes\r\n\r\nFixes #8108.\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\n\r\nFixes the serveForbiddenOrigins flag to allow both invalid and forbidden Origins to be served as non-CORS requests.\r\n\r\n## Background Context\r\n\r\nPreviously the test in CORSCommonSpec used the Origin `http://www.example.com` in the \"forbidden\" test case (line 75). This Origin is the same as the Host set on the default FakeRequest. This meant that the test case would pass, as it would be recognized as a same-origin request.\r\n\r\nThe Origin on the forbidden test case has been changed to one that is neither in the whitelist, nor the Host on the default FakeRequest. Added an additional case within filterRequest in AbstractCORSPolicy to match a non-empty, valid Origin with the serveForbiddenOrigins flag set.\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\nAre there any relevant issues / PRs / mailing lists discussions?\r\n\r\n## Other\r\n\r\nNo new files so no copyright headers needed. I'm not actually sure if the Java implementation has this flag available? I couldn't find anything looking through the java.play.filters classes, but I haven't used Java Play pretty much at all, so I'm not sure.\r\n\r\nNo documentation updates needed as this is a fix.\r\n\r\nIs it possible to get this backported to 2.5.x?\r\n  ","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/playframework/playframework/issues/8134/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/playframework/playframework/issues/8134/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/playframework/playframework/issues/comments/355124101","html_url":"https://github.com/playframework/playframework/issues/